The Minister of Youths and Sports Development, Chief Sunday Dare has redeemed his pledge of cash donation to the Sports Writers Association of Nigeria (SWAN), Oyo State Chapter. Sunday Dare who promised to give the cash donation to the Oyo chapter of the association while speaking at the final of the Oyo SWAN Cup last December has since been deposited into the Associationâ€™s account for accountability. As hinted by the Chairman of Oyo SWAN, Niyi Alebiosu in December, the money will be distributed as prizes among the champions, runners up and third-placed competitors of the football and table tennis competitions held during the last SWAN Week. According to him, the prizes will be presented to the beneficiaries at the 2022 Oyo SWAN Ramadan Lecture coming up on the 19th of April 2022 at the NUJ Press Centre. He added that those to receive their prizes on the day are the five a side football competition champions (BCOS), its runners up (Agidigbo) and the third-placed team (King FM). Others are the Table Tennis Competition Champion, Sola Oladapo of Federal Information, Raji Adebayo of Daily Independent (second) and the third position in the competition.